      partitioning: ["Partition order and orchestration data by market then orderId; keep each order in one ownership cell.", "Shard discovery and courier supply by geospatial cell; isolate chain-wide menu updates from local order traffic."],
      consistency: ["Order transitions, price snapshot, and financial ledger writes are strongly consistent per order.", "Search availability, courier ETA, and merchant capacity are bounded-stale and revalidated before commitment."],
      concurrency: ["Versioned order commands and a legal transition table reject duplicate or late merchant/courier actions.", "A courier lease prevents double assignment; menuVersion and quote expiry prevent ambiguous price changes."],
      asynchronous: ["Merchant dispatch, courier matching, notifications, fraud, settlement, search indexing, and reconciliation consume order events.", "Deadline messages trigger merchant timeout, courier reassignment, cancellation, and compensating refund paths."],
      failures: ["Merchant channel outage leaves order pending; retry across tablet/POS channels then cancel before capture according to policy.", "No courier after acceptance triggers wider search, ETA update, incentive, or controlled cancellation.", "Payment provider uncertainty enters PAYMENT_REVIEW and reconciles by provider reference rather than retrying an unknown charge."],
      retry: ["Order create is idempotent on customer plus key and binds to the quote hash; every saga command carries orderId and step.", "Partner events deduplicate by source eventId; payment and refunds use stable ledger-derived provider keys."],
      security: ["Tokenize cards, mask customer/courier contact, reveal addresses only for active fulfillment, and audit merchant access.", "Sign POS webhooks, validate menu inputs, protect proof-of-delivery media, and segregate financial and location retention."],
      observability: ["Measure browse/quote/order latency and funnel conversion, then accepted-to-prep/pickup/delivery times by market.", "Track orders stuck per state, deadline expirations, courier-location freshness, menu index lag, and payment uncertainty.", "Trace by orderId across orchestrator steps while keeping PII out of logs and metrics."],
      bottlenecks: ["Lunch and dinner create synchronized neighborhood spikes across browse, merchant capacity, couriers, and payment.", "Large chain menu updates and global promotions can invalidate caches and saturate indexing during peak ordering."],
      tradeoffs: ["Orchestration gives support teams an explicit order state and compensation path; choreography reduces central coupling but obscures deadlines.", "Early courier dispatch improves pickup time but wastes supply when prep forecasts are wrong."],
      alternatives: ["Merchant-delivered orders can bypass courier dispatch while sharing checkout, order, and settlement primitives.", "A workflow engine reduces custom timer logic but adds operational dependency and workflow versioning concerns."],
      mvp: ["One market, PostgreSQL orders/menus, OpenSearch discovery, merchant tablet polling, simple courier assignment, and one payment provider.", "Use a versioned state machine, price snapshots, manual exception queues, and basic reconciliation from day one."],
      intermediate: ["Add Kafka/outbox, orchestration deadlines, geo dispatch, dynamic prep estimates, POS webhooks, and settlement ledgers.", "Split discovery, ordering, dispatch, and payments along ownership boundaries while retaining end-to-end order tracing."],
      internetScale: ["Operate market cells with local search, ordering, dispatch, and partner capacity; use global control planes for catalog and identity.", "Apply adaptive caching, learned ETA/dispatch, automated exception remediation, and durable replayable business events."],
      multiRegion: ["Pin an order to its market's write region and replicate its audit trail; active trips do not span regions.", "Fail markets with fenced order/courier ownership and replay outbox events; keep global menu distribution asynchronous and versioned."],
      cost: ["Courier incentives and marketplace operations dominate business cost; technically, maps, search, notifications, and location streaming lead.", "Reduce telemetry frequency outside active deliveries and share versioned menu objects across restaurant locations when semantics allow."],
