      partitioning: ["Partition article processing by publisher/article hash and story clustering by language/topic/time locality.", "Partition feed candidates by edition/topic; hot breaking stories are replicated, not forced through one story shard."],
      consistency: ["Article revisions and publisher rights are versioned authoritative facts; story membership and personalized ranking are eventual.", "Retractions and legal removals use an immediate serving filter with audited propagation SLO."],
      concurrency: ["Revision numbers prevent late connector fetches from overwriting newer corrections.", "Cluster merges/splits use deterministic winner IDs and versioned membership events so replay converges."],
      asynchronous: ["Extraction, translation, embeddings, clustering, moderation, indexing, trending, and feature updates form replayable stages.", "Urgent publisher corrections bypass normal bulk enrichment to patch serving metadata first, then recompute fully."],
